-- Novolipetsk Steel Names Oleg Bagrin Candidate for President
-- B y   A n a t o l y   T e m k i n
-- 2012-09-26T13:22:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-26/novolipetsk-steel-names-oleg-bagrin-candidate-for-president-1-.html
OAO Novolipetsk Steel, the Russian
steelmaker controlled by billionaire  Vladimir Lisin , named  Oleg
Bagrin  as the sole candidate to become the company’s president.  The board nominated Bagrin today, the company said in a
regulatory statement. The shareholders of NLMK, as the company
is known, will vote to elect a president on Oct. 25.  Bagrin has been a member of NLMK’s board since 2004. He was
appointed executive vice president last month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
